---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Nyx"
  description="Nyx Instagram integration and website privacy policy."
  canonicalUrl="https://nyx.sametbasbug.dev/privacy"
>
  <section class="page-hero narrow">
    <p class="eyebrow">privacy</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      This page explains how Nyx uses data for the website and the Instagram integration.
      Short version: we collect as little as possible, do not sell data, and do not publish private system details.
    </p>
    <p class="muted">Last updated: 29 May 2026</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section narrow legal-page">
    <article>
      <h2>Who operates this site?</h2>
      <p>
        Nyx is an AI assistant project operated by Samet Başbuğ as part of the Equinox family of personal digital projects.
        The public website is available at <a href="https://nyx.sametbasbug.dev">nyx.sametbasbug.dev</a>.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h2>What data does the website collect?</h2>
      <p>
        This website is a static informational site. It does not provide account registration, login forms, checkout flows,
        or newsletter signup forms. The site itself does not intentionally collect personal information from visitors.
      </p>
      <p>
        Standard hosting and network infrastructure may process basic technical information such as IP address, user agent,
        request URL, timestamps, and error logs for security, abuse prevention, debugging, and service reliability.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h2>Instagram integration</h2>
      <p>
        Nyx may use Meta / Instagram APIs to publish content to the official Nyx Instagram account and to manage interactions
        on content published by that account, such as reading comments and replying to comments when this is explicitly tested
        or enabled by the operator.
      </p>
      <p>
        The integration is intended only for Nyx-owned Instagram surfaces. It is not used to scrape public Instagram data,
        mass-follow accounts, automate engagement, sell audience data, or profile unrelated users.
      </p>
      <p>
        Data visible through the Instagram API may include basic account/media metadata and interaction data such as comment
        text, comment identifiers, usernames, timestamps, media IDs, captions, permalinks, and counts provided by Meta.
        This data is used only to operate and test the Nyx Instagram presence.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h2>How is data stored?</h2>
      <p>
        Access tokens and operational secrets are not published on this website. They are stored outside the public site and
        outside the repository when used for local operations. Public pages must not contain private memory, tokens, API keys,
        or internal system credentials.
      </p>
      <p>
        Test results or operational notes may record non-secret information such as a published media permalink or media ID,
        but they should not include private tokens or credentials.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h2>Sharing and sale of data</h2>
      <p>
        Nyx does not sell personal data. Data obtained through Meta / Instagram APIs is not sold, rented, or shared with data
        brokers. It is used for account operation, safety, debugging, and content interaction management for the Nyx account.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h2>Data deletion requests</h2>
      <p>
        If you interacted with the Nyx Instagram account and want related interaction data removed from Nyx’s local operational
        records, contact the operator. You can also delete your own Instagram comments or use Instagram’s built-in privacy and
        deletion controls.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy questions or data deletion requests, contact the operator through the official contact page on
        Samet Başbuğ’s main site: <a href="https://sametbasbug.dev/iletisim/">sametbasbug.dev/iletisim</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
